sec.p:
We present a case of monoclonal gammopathy-related auto-inflammatory syndrome distinguished from Schnitzler’s syndrome by complement activation, neutropenia and an absent response to anakinra. We believe that this patient manifests a new auto-inflammatory syndrome not previously described. Features of the syndrome include:
monoclonal paraprotein;
ongoing classical pathway complement consumption;
intermittent fever, rash and hypotension;
transient leucopenia and thrombocytopenia, and severe complement depletion following initial symptoms;
resistance to IL1 antagonists; and
acute attacks terminated by corticosteroids.
